\begin_layout Subsection
Cross-sectional Evidence
\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Table 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "tab: Xsection"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 presents the result of a pooled cross-sectional regression estimating relation
 between effective inventor shares and the HHI for the 1997 and 2012 samples:
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{equation}
\text{Share Inventors}{}_{p,t}=f_{k,t}\mathbf{1}\left\{ p\in k\right\} +\beta\text{HHI}_{p,t}+\beta_{2012}\times\bm{1}\left\{ t=2012\right\} \text{HHI}_{p,t}+\gamma\log\text{Sales}_{p,t}+\gamma_{2012}\times\bm{1}\left\{ t=2012\right\} \log\text{Sales}_{p,t}+\varepsilon_{p},\label{eq: Xsec}
\end{equation}

\end_inset

where the variables are defined as in the main sample.
 In both periods the coefficient for the HHI is positive, although it is
 only significant in 2012.
 Importantly, the coefficient 
\begin_inset Formula $\beta_{2012}$
\end_inset

, corresponding to the interaction between the indicator for 2012 and the
 HHI is positive and significant, denoting an increase in the slope of the
 relation between inventor shares and concentration, providing further evidence
 in favor of the mechanism described in the main text.
\end_layout

