 levels 
\begin_inset Formula $\left(+\ p<0.1,^{*}\ p<0.05,^{**}\ p<.01,^{***}\ p<.001\right)$
\end_inset

.
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

6d Lerner Index
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 refers to the Lerner Index constructed as in 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq: Lerner"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

on NAICS 6-digits averaged at the 4-digit NAICS level weighting by the value
 of shipments; 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

4d Lerner Index
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

 is computed using 4-digit aggregates for the value of shipments, payroll
 and costs, summing over the NAICS 6-digit composing each sector.
 
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

